<a class="definition-word" data-category="general-biology" id="transformation">Transformation</a> - The process of introducing new genetic material into cells, mostly used when talking about <a href="#bacteria">bacterial</a> cells (similar to <a href="#transfection">transfection</a> in <a href="#mammal">mammalian</a> cells). Transformation can be performed by electrical and or chemical means, <em>exempli gratia</em> <a href="#electroporation">electroporation</a>.